Done. Feature #9 (drift detection module) is implemented and committed. 

**What was built:**

- **`src/svapna/evaluate/drift.py`** — Compares ICT reports across runs with:
  - `load_ict_report()` — deserializes ICT JSON back into dataclasses
  - `compare_dimensions()` — computes per-dimension deltas
  - `detect_red_flags()` — catches all 5 patterns from evaluation.md (generic preamble, values inversion, voice flattening, sycophancy increase, loss of uncertainty)
  - `compare_anchor_prompts()` — uses anchor prompt IDs from identity.yml as canaries
  - `detect_drift()` / `detect_drift_from_files()` — main entry points producing `DriftReport` with actionable findings
  - `DriftConfig` — loads thresholds from config/identity.yml

- **`tests/test_drift.py`** — 35 tests covering all 5 test cases plus edge cases, all passing
